-pretag id="sdPretag14243402327840" parent-tag-id="197">G6P</sd-pretag> which enters the oxidative PPP. The resulting <sd-pretag id="sdPretag14243402444460" parent-tag-id="199">NADPH</sd-pretag> is utilized for regeneration of reduced <sd-pretag id="sdPretag14243402918570" parent-tag-id="198">glutathione</sd-pretag>. 1,3‐DPG, 1,3‐diphosphoglycerate; GSSG, <sd-pretag id="sdPretag14243402918571" parent-tag-id="198">glutathione</sd-pretag> disulfide; GSH, reduced <sd-pretag id="sdPretag14243402918572" parent-tag-id="198">glutathione</sd-pretag>. <graphic href="https://api.sourcedata.io/file.php?panel_id=2529"/></sd-panel><sd-panel panel_id="2530"><b>(C and D)</b> <sd-tag id="sdTag192" source="sdapi" category="None" entity_type="molecule" role="assayed" text="DHAP" ext_ids="CHEBI:16108" ext_dbs="" in_caption="True" ext_names="glycerone phosphate" ext_tax_ids="" ext_tax_names="" ext_urls="http://www.ebi.ac.uk/chebi/searchId.do?chebiId=">DHAP</sd-tag>, <sd-tag id="sdTag193" source="sdapi" category="None" entity_type="molecule" role="assayed" text="S7P" ext_ids="CHEBI:15721" ext_dbs="" in_caption="True" ext_names="sedoheptulose 7-phosphate" ext_tax_ids="" ext_tax_names="" ext_urls="http://www.ebi.ac.uk/chebi/searchId.do?chebiId=">S7P</sd-tag>, <sd-tag id="sdTag197" source="sdapi" category="None" entity_type="molecule" role="assayed" text="G6P" ext_ids="CHEBI:14314" ext_dbs="" in_caption="True" ext_names="D-glucose 6-phosphate" ext_tax_ids="" ext_tax_names="" ext_urls="http://www.ebi.ac.uk/chebi/searchId.do?chebiId=">G6P</sd-tag>, and <sd-tag id="sdTag198" source="sdapi" category="None" entity_type="molecule" role="assayed" text="glutathione" ext_ids="CHEBI:16856" ext_dbs="" in_caption="True" ext_names="glutathione" ext_tax_ids="" ext_tax_names="" ext_urls="http://www.ebi.ac.uk/chebi/searchId.do?chebiId=">glutathione</sd-tag> levels and <sd-tag id="sdTag199" source="sdapi" category="None" entity_type="molecule" role="assayed" text="NADPH" ext_ids="CHEBI:16474" ext_dbs="" in